00:08:55.120 --> 00:09:08.120
In many Bibles produced by Christendom, the term gives the idea of a spirit creature in heaven, even a holy ghost, sometimes even a holy demon.

00:09:08.120 --> 00:09:12.120
That must be very confusing to the readers.

00:09:12.120 --> 00:09:15.120
But what can the translators do about that?

00:09:15.120 --> 00:09:23.120
In many languages, our translators have found that the closest way to translate holy spirit is to say holy power or holy force.

00:09:23.120 --> 00:09:28.120
This may sound very different, but it conveys the same idea.

00:09:28.120 --> 00:09:39.120
And even the English New World Translation describes the term holy spirit as God's active force, at Genesis 1-2, while other English translations say God's Holy Spirit.

00:09:39.120 --> 00:09:47.120
So now the brothers can use an expression that is understood by the field and the audience.

00:09:47.120 --> 00:09:51.120
But it must be a wonderful thing to have the new world translation.

00:09:51.120 --> 00:09:53.120
Yes, it's a wonderful thing.

00:09:53.120 --> 00:09:57.120
But still, the brothers have to get used to the new terms.

00:09:57.120 --> 00:10:05.120
Remember that they've been using the original terms in their local Bibles for years to teach people the truth.

00:10:05.120 --> 00:10:15.120
